<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Tomato Hooks with String for Greenhouse Growing</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    Simple hook-and-string setups work — until plant growth outpaces your ability to manage them.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, the best tomato hooks with string are durable, preloaded systems that provide consistent support, but they work best when paired with a plan for managing plant height over time.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Hook-and-string systems are one of the simplest ways to support tomatoes in a greenhouse. They’re easy to set up, reliable, and work well early in the season.
  </p>
  <p>
    The challenge shows up later — when plants keep growing and the system doesn’t adjust.
  </p>
